Class BankCoupledModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.models.Model
      • fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.models.CoupledModel
        • fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.examples.bank.BankCoupledModel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    VariableDefinitionsAndSharingI, VariableInitialisationI, CoupledModelI, ModelI, java.io.Serializable

    public class BankCoupledModel
extends CoupledModel
    The class BankCoupledModel is the coupled model used in the bank example to tie together the two atomic models client generator and bank.

    Description

    Nothing specific in this coupled model. It simply provides a concrete class from the abstract class CoupledModel and chooses the constructor to be used for its instantiation. The simulation report used for this model is the predefined standard report for coupled models.

    Invariant

     invariant       true        // no more invariants

    Created on : 2022-09-13

    Author:

        Parameters:
        uri - URI of the coupled model to be created.
        simulatedTimeUnit - time unit used in the simulation by the model.
        simulationEngine - simulation engine enacting the model.
        submodels - array of submodels of the new coupled model.
        imported - map from imported event types to submodels consuming them.
        reexported - map from event types exported by submodels that are reexported by this coupled model.
        connections - map connecting event sources to arrays of event sinks among submodels.
